headline: Molina Healthcare Stock Falls 27%. Why Its Earnings Outlook Is So Bleak.
summary: Molina Healthcare stock tanked ahead of the open Friday after the insurer issued a disappointing earnings outlook for 2026.  Amid broad concerns across the healthcare sector,  Molina  shares were down 27% in premarket trading Friday after the company reported its fourth-quarter earnings late Thursday.  Molina posted a loss of $2.75 per share on revenue of $11.4 billion.

headline: S&P 500 Health Insurer Dives As ACA Enrollment Implodes
summary: S&P 500 health insurer Molina Healthcare crashed to a nearly six-year low on Friday morning after posting an unexpected loss amid surging health benefit costs.  Centene, another S&P 500 member, also reported a loss, though that was anticipated.  Molina said that it expects insured Affordable Care Act Marketplace membership to sink from 713,000 at the end of Q3 to just 220,000 at the end of 2026.

headline: Molina, Centene Fall on Concerns About Medicaid Business
summary: Jittery investors are sending down shares of Medicaid-focused health-insurance companies, with a 28% plunge for Molina Healthcare and a 5% drop for larger rival Centene.  Molina on Thursday night reported fourth-quarter earnings well below analysts’ expectations and offered 2026 guidance that incorporated adjusted earnings per share of less than half the FactSet consensus projection.  Centene offered a more optimistic take.
